---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '@/components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '@/components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service - WYRE Technology"
  description="Terms of Service for the WYRE MCP Gateway and MSP Claude Plugins."
>
  <Header />

  <main class="flex-1 py-16">
    <div class="container max-w-3xl">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="text-[var(--muted)] mb-10">Last updated: March 25, 2026</p>

      <div class="prose prose-neutral dark:prose-invert max-w-none space-y-8 text-[var(--text)]">

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
          <p class="text-[var(--muted)] leading-relaxed">
            By accessing or using the Wyre Technology MCP Gateway and related services ("Service"), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service. If you do not agree, do not use the Service.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">2. Definitions</h2>
          <ul class="text-[var(--muted)] leading-relaxed space-y-2 list-disc pl-5">
            <li><strong>"AI Services"</strong> refers to the artificial intelligence-based services provided through the Service, including AI-driven tool calls, process automation, and AI-assisted interactions with third-party platforms.</li>
            <li><strong>"AI-Generated Outputs"</strong> means any data, content, analyses, actions, or other results generated by AI services as a result of processing your data or through interactions with your connected systems.</li>
            <li><strong>"Third-Party Platforms"</strong> means any external services connected through the Service, including but not limited to Autotask, Datto RMM, IT Glue, HaloPSA, NinjaOne, ConnectWise, Syncro, Atera, SuperOps, and any other MSP platforms.</li>
            <li><strong>"Tool Calls"</strong> means any actions executed on Third-Party Platforms through the Service on your behalf, including but not limited to creating, reading, updating, or deleting data.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">3. Description of Service</h2>
          <p class="text-[var(--muted)] leading-relaxed">
            The Service provides a hosted proxy that connects AI assistants (including Claude by Anthropic) to Third-Party Platforms via the Model Context Protocol (MCP). The Service stores encrypted API credentials on your behalf and proxies requests between AI assistants and those platforms. The Service acts as a pass-through proxy and does not independently verify, approve, or undo any operations performed on connected platforms.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">4. Your Responsibilities</h2>
          <p class="text-[var(--muted)] leading-relaxed mb-3">You agree to the following obligations:</p>
          <ul class="text-[var(--muted)] leading-relaxed space-y-2 list-disc pl-5">
            <li><strong>Credential Security.</strong> You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account credentials and any API keys you provide to the Service.</li>
            <li><strong>Authority.</strong> You must have the right and authority to submit any API keys or credentials you provide to the Service.</li>
            <li><strong>Third-Party Compliance.</strong> You must comply with the terms of service of any Third-Party Platforms you connect through the Service.</li>
            <li><strong>Lawful Use.</strong> You must not use the Service for any unlawful purpose or in violation of any regulations applicable to you, including data protection and privacy laws, intellectual property rights laws, and any specific regulations governing your industry.</li>
            <li><strong>Ethical Use of AI.</strong> You agree to use the AI Services and any related technologies ethically, in a manner that respects privacy rights, avoids discrimination, and complies with applicable ethical guidelines.</li>
            <li><strong>Review and Validation.</strong> You assume full responsibility for the selection of the AI Services to achieve your intended results and for the use and results obtained from the AI Services. You acknowledge that you must regularly review and validate AI-generated outputs and Tool Call results for accuracy and appropriateness before relying on them.</li>
            <li><strong>Data Backups.</strong> You are solely responsible for maintaining adequate backups of your data on connected Third-Party Platforms. You acknowledge that Tool Calls executed through the Service may create, modify, or delete data on those platforms, and that such actions may be irreversible.</li>
            <li><strong>Access Controls.</strong> You are responsible for implementing appropriate access controls on connected platforms, including using read-only API keys where write access is not required.</li>
            <li><strong>Notification of Issues.</strong> You shall promptly notify Wyre Technology of any issues, concerns, or malfunctions related to the Service, and agree to provide detailed information about such issues to aid in their resolution.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">5. API Credentials and Data</h2>
          <p class="text-[var(--muted)] leading-relaxed">
            Credentials you submit are encrypted at rest using AES-256 encryption and are only decrypted in memory to fulfill proxied requests. We do not sell, share, or use your credentials for any purpose other than fulfilling your requests. You may delete your credentials and account at any time. Upon termination, your stored credentials will be deleted within 30 days unless you request immediate deletion.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">6. Acceptable Use</h2>
          <p class="text-[var(--muted)] leading-relaxed">
            You agree not to:
